Expressions representing numbers may be combined with operators (such as +as numeric addition operator + (for numeric addition) + or arithmeticoperators for * (multiplication operator) * (multiplication) *) to form a compound expression operator combination compound expression that represents the application of a corresponding primitive function to those numbers. For example,
